form.allowRevotingDescription: This will allow members to change their vote on proposals before the voting duration deadline. As a result, proposals will not be able to finish early.
form.allowedMethodsDescription: Comma separated list of smart contract method names to authorize (i.e. set_item, remove_item)
form.approverDescription: Specify a DAO that must approve proposals before they can be voted on. This does not currently work with multiple choice proposals.
form.authzCustomMessageTypeTooltip: Use a custom protobuf message type. WARNING: do not use this feature unless you know what you're doing.
form.authzLimitsDescription: Limitations to put on the Authorzation grant.

form.automaticallyAddTokensTooltip: Should tokens sent to the DAO get added to the treasury?
form.callsDescription: The maximum amount of times the designated account is authorized to call a smart contract.
form.contractPermissionsDescription: The contract permissions this authorization grants the grantee.
form.contributionAttributesDescription: These are the values for which raters will be asked to provide ratings on contributions, and the associated tokens comprise the compensation paid out for that attribute. For example, "Community impact", "Financial value", "Code quality", etc.
form.contributionInstructionsPlaceholder: This is what contributors will see when they submit their contributions. Explain how they should submit.
form.contributionSubmitted: You submitted a contribution for this cycle. Submitting again will overwrite your previous response.
form.createValidatorMessageTooltip: Create a validator controlled by your DAO. Note: you will need to run a validator node (on a server for example). Be sure to use that node's public key (<binary> tendermint show-validator).
form.dragFileHereOrClick: Drag file here or <2>click</2> to select.
form.dragImageHereOrClick: Drag image here or <2>click</2> to select.

form.earlyExecuteTooltip: If the vetoer decides NOT to veto a passed proposal, this allows them to execute the proposal instead, effectively skipping the timelock duration and speeding up the governance process.
form.editValidatorMessageTooltip: Update the information of a validator controlled by your DAO.
form.encodedMessagesTooltip: Provide a list of protobuf encoded messages with the values in base64.
form.executeSmartContractTooltip: When sending an NFT to a smart contract, you may want to trigger an execution with an optional message on the contract. If you don't know what this means, you probably don't want to use it.
form.expeditedDescription: Expedited proposals have a shorter voting duration and higher voting threshold.
form.feeShareContractAddressDescription: The address to claim fee share for. NOTE: you must be admin or the creator of this smart contract to claim fees for it.
form.feeShareToggleWithdrawerAddressTooltip_d: Customize the address allowed to withdraw fees. Defaults to the DAO.
form.feeShareToggleWithdrawerAddressTooltip_g: Customize the address allowed to withdraw fees. Defaults to the chain's governance module.
form.feeShareToggleWithdrawerAddressTooltip_w: Customize the address allowed to withdraw fees. Defaults to your wallet.
form.feeShareWithdrawerAddressTooltip: The address that can withdraw fees.
form.governanceTokenNamePlaceholder: Longer name of your token (e.g. "Dog Dao token")
form.granteeAddressTooltip: The address you are granting or revoking to execute a message on behalf of the DAO.
form.ibcTimeoutTooltip: In rare cases, an IBC transaction may fail to relay to the destination chain. A timeout is required to prevent failed transactions from retrying forever and unexpectedly executing in the future. A good timeout is probably a few days to a week after execution. Since passing a proposal takes time, this timeout will be added to the end of the voting period automatically.
form.ibcTimeoutTooltip_blocks: In rare cases, an IBC transaction may fail to relay to the destination chain. A timeout is required to prevent failed transactions from retrying forever and unexpectedly executing in the future. A good timeout is probably a few days to a week after execution. Since passing a proposal takes time, make sure this timeout is long enough to cover the entire voting period. This DAO uses a block height-based voting period, so the timeout cannot be added automatically.
form.ibcTimeoutTooltip_created: In rare cases, an IBC transaction may fail to relay to the destination chain. A timeout is required to prevent failed transactions from retrying forever and unexpectedly executing in the future. A good timeout is probably a few days to a week after execution.
form.imageUrlTooltip: A link to an image. For example: https://moonphase.is/image.svg
form.itemNoValueSet: This item does not currently have a value set.
form.itemValueEmpty: This item is currently set to an empty value.
form.membersToAddOrUpdateDescription: Set the voting power of each member individually. DAO DAO will calculate the voting weight percentage for you.
form.migrateDescription: This will <1>migrate</1> the selected contract to a new code ID.
form.multipleChoiceDescription: This allows proposals to contain multiple choices instead of just `Yes` and `No`.
form.multipleChoiceOptionDescriptionPlacehold: Give your choice a description... (supports Markdown format)
form.name: Name
form.nftMintInstructions: Create a unique token ID for the NFT and enter the address of the initial owner below.
form.nftUploadMetadataInstructions: Input the NFT's metadata, and then press 'Upload' to store it on IPFS.
form.onlyMembersExecuteTooltip: If enabled, only members may execute passed proposals.
form.passingThresholdDescription:
The proportion of voters on a single choice (Yes/No/Abstain) proposal who must vote 'Yes' for it to pass. Passing threshold works differently depending on whether your DAO has a quorum.
- If your DAO *has a quorum*, the passing threshold is only calculated from those who voted.
- If your DAO has *no quorum*, this is the percentage of the DAO's voting power that must vote 'yes' for a proposal to pass.
form.passingThresholdWithQuorumDescription: The proportion of those who voted on a single choice proposal who must vote 'Yes' for it to pass.
form.percentOfTotalSupplyTooltip: {{weight}} of the total token supply will be split evenly among all of the members in this tier. Want to add members with different voting power? Add another tier.
form.proposalDepositDescription: The number of tokens that must be deposited to create a proposal. Setting this may deter spam, but setting it too high may limit broad participation.
form.proposalSubmissionPolicyDescription: Who is allowed to submit proposals to the DAO?
form.proposalsDescriptionPlaceholder: Give your proposal a description (supports Markdown)...
form.quorumDescription: The minimum percentage of voting power that must vote on a proposal for it to be considered. For example, in the US House of Representatives, 218 members must be present for a vote. If you have a DAO with many inactive members, setting this value too high may make it difficult to pass proposals.
form.quorumDescription_create:
The minimum percentage of voting power that must vote on a proposal for it to be considered. For example, in the US House of Representatives, 218 members must be present for a vote. If you have a DAO with many inactive members, setting this value too high may make it difficult to pass proposals.

*If not using a quorum for the single choice proposal passing threshold, this quorum will only apply to multiple choice proposals.*
form.ratingInstructionsPlaceholder: This is what DAO members will see when they are rating the contributions. Explain how they should rate.
form.ratingsSubmitted: You submitted ratings for this cycle. Submitting again will overwrite your previous response.
form.redelegateDestinationValidatorTooltip: The validator you are redelegating to.
form.redelegateSourceValidatorTooltip: The validator you are redelegating away from.
form.refundFailedProposalsTooltip: Should failed proposals have their deposit refunded?
form.refundPolicyTitle: Once a proposal completes, when should deposits be refunded?
form.requireProposalDepositTooltip: If enabled, requires that tokens are deposited to create a proposal.
form.sameAsPublicSubmissionCloseDate: Same as public submission close date
form.showAdvancedNftFieldsTooltip: The form above only allows setting name and description in the metadata attached to the image. Turn this on to view more advanced fields.
form.smartContractMessageDescription: The smart contract message to execute.
form.spendingAllowanceDescription: The amount of funds allowed to be spent by the authorized account.
form.tierNameTooltip: The "class" of member. For example: "Core developers" or "friends and family." These names are only for your reference.
form.timelockDurationTooltip: The duration of time after a proposal's voting period expires during which it can be vetoed. The proposal cannot be executed until this timelock expires. If a proposal passes early due to sufficient voting turnout, the timelock still applies after the proposal's entire voting period (and NOT the early pass time).
form.title: Title
form.tokenSwapCreateInstructions: In this step, you will create the token swap. This creation step describes how many funds each party needs to send for the swap to complete. <2>No funds will be transferred at this time.</2>
form.tokenSwapExistingInstructions: In this step, you will choose a token swap that you (or the counterparty) has already initiated. After you fund a swap, you can withdraw the tokens you funded unless (or until) the counterparty has paid. Likewise, the counterparty can withdraw the tokens they funded until you pay.
form.unjailValidatorMessageTooltip: When a validator is 'jailed' for downtime, you must submit an Unjail transaction from the operator account in order to be able to get block proposer rewards again.
form.unstakingDurationDescription: In order to vote, members must stake their tokens with the DAO. Members who would like to leave the DAO or trade their governance tokens must first unstake them. This setting configures how long members have to wait after unstaking their tokens for those tokens to become available. The longer you set this duration, the more sure you can be sure that people who register their tokens are keen to participate in your DAO's governance.
form.updateAdminDescription: This will update the admin for the selected contract. The new admin will have complete control over the contract. Take care.
form.updateProposalSubmissionConfigDescriptio: This will update the proposal submission configuration for this DAO. A bad configuration can lock the DAO. Take care. If you have questions, please feel free to ask in the <2>DAO DAO Discord</2>.
form.updateVotingConfigDescription: This will update the voting configuration for this DAO. A bad configuration can lock the DAO or create unexpected voting outcomes. Take care. If you have questions, please feel free to ask in the <2>DAO DAO Discord</2>.
form.uploadNewFileQuestion: Would you like to use a different file?
form.useCw20ExecuteTooltip: Fund the smart contract execution with a CW20 token instead of a native token.
form.useDirectIbcPathTooltip: When enabled, avoid using the optimized multi-hop path. This may result in an undesirable IBC token on the final chain.
form.vetoBeforePassedTooltip: This allows the vetoer to veto a proposal while it is still open for voting (i.e. before it passes). Voting is still allowed for the entire voting period so that voters may express their preferences, but the proposal will never be executable once vetoed.
form.votingDurationDescription: The amount of time proposals are open for voting. A low proposal duration may increase the speed at which your DAO can pass proposals. Setting the duration too low may make it difficult for proposals to pass as voters will have limited time to vote. After this time elapses, the proposal will either pass or fail.
form.votingWeightPerMemberTooltip: Each member of this tier will receive {{weight}} voting power. Want to add members with different voting power? Add another tier.
form.whatReceiveCounterpartyQuestion: What do you need to <2>receive</2> from the counterparty for the token swap to complete?
form.whatSendCounterpartyQuestion: What do you need to <2>send</2> to the counterparty for the token swap to complete?
form.whoTransferNftQuestion: Where would you like to transfer the NFT?

info.approvalProposalExplanation_approved: This proposal was accepted by the approver.
info.approvalProposalExplanation_pending: This proposal is waiting to be accepted by the approver so that it can open for voting.
info.approvalProposalExplanation_rejected: This proposal was not allowed to open for voting because the approver rejected it.
info.approverEnabledNoMultipleChoice: Approver is enabled, which is currently incompatible with multiple choice proposals.
info.approverExplanation_choosing: DAOs shown below have this DAO ({{daoName}}) set as their approver. This action completes the approval setup process by enabling the creation of approval proposals in {{daoName}} when the selected DAO below attempts to create a new proposal.
info.approverExplanation_chose: The DAO shown below has this DAO ({{daoName}}) set as their approver. This action completes the approval setup process by enabling the creation of approval proposals in {{daoName}} when the selected DAO below attempts to create a new proposal.
info.approverProposalExplanation_closed: This proposal is responsible for approving a proposal in another DAO. Since it was rejected and closed, the original proposal was not allowed to open for voting.
info.approverProposalExplanation_executed: This proposal is responsible for approving a proposal in another DAO. Since it was passed and executed, the original proposal opened for voting.
info.approverProposalExplanation_execution_fa: This proposal is responsible for approving a proposal in another DAO. An unexpected error occurred (execution failed). Something is wrong.
info.approverProposalExplanation_open: This proposal is responsible for approving a proposal in another DAO. If this proposal is passed and executed, the original proposal will open for voting.
info.approverProposalExplanation_passed: This proposal is responsible for approving a proposal in another DAO. Now that it passed, it must be executed in order to open the original proposal for voting.
info.approverProposalExplanation_rejected: This proposal is responsible for approving a proposal in another DAO. Now that it was rejected, it must be closed in order to mark the original proposal as denied.
info.appsProposalDescription: Add a title and description, and then review the actions generated by the app. Once it all looks good, publish it to the DAO for voting.
info.authzAuthorizationDescription: Grant / revoke authorizations that allow other accounts to perform actions on behalf of the DAO.

info.availableHistoryLoaded: All available history has been loaded.
info.betterNonPfmIbcPathAvailable: A better path exists that unwinds the IBC token properly, but it requires hops that cannot be performed in a single proposal due to the configuration of one or more of the chains involved. You may safely use the direct path above, though it likely results in an undesirable IBC token on the final chain that will eventually need to be unwound. If you wish to unwind it manually, follow the path below by creating an individual proposal for the first hop, then a second proposal once the first one is passed and executed, and so on.
info.betterPfmIbcPathAvailable_one: A better path exists that unwinds the IBC token properly, but it requires you to have an account on {{chains}}. An account must exist on each intermediary chain in a multi-hop transaction to act as a failsafe in the event of catastrophic failure (unlikely). Either a cross-chain or ICA account works and will be automatically detected once created. You may safely use the direct path above, though it likely results in an undesirable IBC token on the final chain that will eventually need to be unwound.
info.betterPfmIbcPathAvailable_other: A better path exists that unwinds the IBC token properly, but it requires you to have accounts on the following chains: {{chains}}. An account must exist on each intermediary chain in a multi-hop transaction to act as a failsafe in the event of catastrophic failure (unlikely). Either a cross-chain or ICA account works and will be automatically detected once created. You may safely use the direct path above, though it likely results in an undesirable IBC token on the final chain that will eventually need to be unwound.
info.bulkImportActionExplanation: Choose a JSON or CSV file below that matches the format described in <2>this guide</2>.

Clicking the button below begins the registration process; it will take you to Discord's website and prompt you to choose a server and channel. You will then be redirected back here and prompted to authorize with your wallet. Once this is done, proposal notifications are enabled.

info.enableMultipleChoiceProposalsExplanation: This action will enable the creation of multiple choice proposals, which allow voting on many options in one proposal. Your wallet is your digital identity on the blockchain. Having one lets you interact with web3 applications like DAO DAO.
We recommend the Keplr wallet.
info.logInToViewMembership: Log in to view your membership status in the DAO.
info.manageIcasDescription: Register or unregister an ICA chain. ICAs must be registered (once created) to be shown in the treasury and used in actions.

info.passingThresholdTooltip_quorum: The proportion of voters who must vote 'Yes' on a single choice proposal for it to pass. Because quorum is enabled, this threshold is calculated only from those who voted.

proposalStatus.canStillBeVetoed: Although the vote is determined, it can still be vetoed. If the veto timelock period expires, then this proposal can be executed.
proposalStatus.completedAndOpen: This proposal's outcome is determined. Votes may still be cast until expiration.
proposalStatus.completedAndOpen_vetoed: This proposal was vetoed. Votes may still be cast until expiration, but it will never pass.
proposalStatus.depositPeriod: This proposal is in the deposit period and will open for voting once the deposit is reached.
proposalStatus.govNotOpen: This proposal is closed for voting with {{turnoutYesPercent}} of voters in favor.
proposalStatus.notOpenMultipleChoice: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}}.
proposalStatus.notOpenMultipleChoice_closed: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}}. It was rejected and closed.
proposalStatus.notOpenMultipleChoice_executed: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutWinningPercent}} of voters voting for {{turnoutWinner}}. It was passed and executed.
proposalStatus.notOpenMultipleChoice_executionFailed: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutWinningPercent}} of voters voting for {{turnoutWinner}}. It was passed but execution failed.
proposalStatus.notOpenMultipleChoice_overruleTimelock: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutWinningPercent}} of voters voting for {{turnoutWinner}}. It is now frozen until overruled or until the overrule period expires, after which it can be executed.
proposalStatus.notOpenMultipleChoice_overruled: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutWinningPercent}} of voters voting for {{turnoutWinner}}. However, it was overruled.
proposalStatus.notOpenMultipleChoice_passed: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutWinningPercent}} of voters voting for {{turnoutWinner}}. It was passed and now needs to be executed.
proposalStatus.notOpenMultipleChoice_rejected: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}}. It was rejected and now needs to be closed.
proposalStatus.notOpenMultipleChoice_vetoTimelock: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutWinningPercent}} of voters voting for {{turnoutWinner}}. It is now frozen until vetoed or until the veto period expires, after which it can be executed.
proposalStatus.notOpenMultipleChoice_vetoedNoWinner: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}}. It was vetoed.
proposalStatus.notOpenMultipleChoice_vetoedWinner: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutWinningPercent}} of voters voting for {{turnoutWinner}}. However, it was vetoed.
proposalStatus.notOpenSingleChoice: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutYesPercent}} of voters in favor.
proposalStatus.notOpenSingleChoice_closed: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutYesPercent}} of voters in favor. It was rejected and closed.
proposalStatus.notOpenSingleChoice_executed: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutYesPercent}} of voters in favor. It was passed and executed.
proposalStatus.notOpenSingleChoice_executionFailed: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutYesPercent}} of voters in favor. It was passed but execution failed.
proposalStatus.notOpenSingleChoice_overruleTimelock: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutYesPercent}} of voters in favor. It is now frozen until overruled or until the overrule period expires, after which it can be executed.
proposalStatus.notOpenSingleChoice_overruledNotPassed: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutYesPercent}} of voters in favor. It was overruled.
proposalStatus.notOpenSingleChoice_overruledPassed: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutYesPercent}} of voters in favor. However, it was overruled.
proposalStatus.notOpenSingleChoice_passed: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutYesPercent}} of voters in favor. It was passed and now needs to be executed.
proposalStatus.notOpenSingleChoice_rejected: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutYesPercent}} of voters in favor. It was rejected and now needs to be closed.
proposalStatus.notOpenSingleChoice_vetoTimelock: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutYesPercent}} of voters in favor. It is now frozen until vetoed or until the veto period expires, after which it can be executed.
proposalStatus.notOpenSingleChoice_vetoedNotPassed: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutYesPercent}} of voters in favor. It was vetoed.
proposalStatus.notOpenSingleChoice_vetoedPassed: This proposal is closed for voting with a turnout of {{turnoutPercent}} and {{turnoutYesPercent}} of voters in favor. However, it was vetoed.
proposalStatus.willFail: If the current vote stands, this proposal will fail.
proposalStatus.willFailBadQuorum: If the current vote stands, this proposal will fail due to a lack of voter participation.
proposalStatus.willFailBadThreshold: If the current vote stands, this proposal will fail because insufficient 'Yes' votes have been cast.
proposalStatus.willFailTiedVote: If the current vote stands, this proposal will fail because the votes are tied.
proposalStatus.willPass: If the current vote stands, this proposal will pass.
proposalStatus.willPass_vetoEnabled: If the current vote stands and this proposal is not vetoed, it will pass.
proposalStatus.willVeto: If the current vote stands, this proposal will be vetoed.

info.proposalThresholdTooltip: A proposal must attain this proportion of 'Yes' votes to pass.
info.pushNotificationsTooltip: Receive inbox notifications on your mobile phone or browser.
info.quorumTooltip_multiple: The minimum amount of voting power that must vote on a proposal for it to be passable. When quorum is not met, even if a winner is chosen, the proposal will be rejected.
info.quorumTooltip_single: The minimum amount of voting power that must vote on a proposal for it to be passable. When quorum is not met, even if the passing threshold is met, the proposal will be rejected.
info.recognizeSubDaoDescription: {{name}} is a legitimate SubDAO. This adds it to the SubDAOs tab.
info.registerIcaDescription: Registering an ICA (once it's created) shows it in the treasury and makes it usable in actions.
info.registerSlashVestingExplanation: <0>When a slash occurs against a validator with whom a vesting contract is currently staking or unstaking tokens, the slash needs to be registered with the vesting contract. For more information, see the Slashing section of the vesting contract's</0><1>security documentation</1><2>.</2>
info.relayingCrossChainMessages: Cross-chain messages are waiting to be relayed. Check back in a few minutes to ensure relaying is complete.
info.removeCw20FromTreasuryActionDescription: Stop displaying the DAO's balance of a CW20 token in the treasury view.
info.removeCw721FromTreasuryActionDescription: Stop displaying the NFTs owned by the DAO from a CW721 NFT collection in the treasury view.
info.retroactiveCompensationDescription: After each contribution cycle, contributors are assigned points based on their contributions. Payment is split based on the points they receive.
info.reviewActionImportData: Review the following actions to make sure they look right. If they do, click the Import button at the bottom to add them to the proposal.
info.revotingTooltip: Whether or not members can change their vote on proposals before voting ends. When enabled, proposals will not be able to finish early.
info.saveTransactionDescription: Save this transaction so you can reuse it later. Using an existing name will overwrite the previous save.
info.selectPressChain: Each post will be minted as an NFT on this chain and then deposited into the DAO's treasury.
info.selfRelayDescription: One or more messages in this proposal require self-relaying across chains since automatic relayers do not exist or are inactive right now.
info.setUpApproverDescription: Set up this DAO as an approver that is responsible for approving another DAO's proposals before they open for voting.
info.socialLoginWarning: Social logins may be less secure than a self-managed wallet. We recommend the self-managed wallets, above, if you plan on storing large amounts of money.
info.socialLoginWarning_onlySocial: Social logins may be less secure than a self-managed wallet. We recommend a self-managed wallet if you plan on storing large amounts of money.
info.spendActionDescription_dao: Spend native or CW20 tokens from the treasury.
info.spendActionDescription_gov: Spend tokens from the community pool.
info.spendActionDescription_wallet: Spend native tokens from your wallet.
info.stakeYourTokensToJoin: Stake your ${{tokenSymbol}} tokens to become a member of {{daoName}}.
info.stakedNftsExplanation: These have been staked by DAO members to earn voting power.
info.stargazeCreateCollectionFirst: On Stargaze, you must first create the NFT Collection via a DAO proposal, and then you can mint NFTs.
info.statusPageDescription: Check the status of DAO DAO's services.
info.subDaoExplanation: SubDAOs are children DAOs that help manage groups within your DAO.
info.subDaoNotYetRecognized: {{child}} has not yet been recognized by {{parent}} as a SubDAO. Be careful interacting with unrecognized SubDAOs as they could be malicious.

info.submissionsBeingRated: Members of the DAO are rating submissions. After the rating period closes, the DAO will publish a proposal to distribute compensation according to their responses.
info.submitGovernanceProposalDescription: Submit a proposal to chain governance.
info.submitUpgradeProposal: Submit a proposal to upgrade the DAO?
info.tierMemberGovTokenAllocationTooltip: This member will receive {{tokens}} ${{tokenSymbol}} when the DAO is created.
info.tokenBurned: NFT with ID {{tokenId}} has been burned.
info.tokenDaoNotMemberInfo_dao: You are not a member of {{daoName}}. To become a member, you must obtain and stake ${{tokenSymbol}}.
info.tokenDaoNotMemberInfo_proposal: You were not a member of {{daoName}} when this proposal was created, so you cannot vote on it. You will be able to vote on future proposals as long as you have ${{tokenSymbol}} staked at the time those proposals are created.
info.tokenSwapDescription: Create a new token swap that completes when both parties have paid their tokens or fund an existing one.
info.tokenSwapExplanation: To perform a token swap, one DAO must first create it, configuring the number of tokens each party must contribute. Then, both DAOs must add their funds. Once both DAOs have added their funds to the swap, the swap will be performed immediately.

info.totalStakedTooltip: The amount of ${{tokenSymbol}} currently staked with the DAO and thus earning voting power.

info.unstakingMechanics: It will take {{humanReadableTime}} from the time you unstake your tokens before they are able to be redeemed by you. During that time, you will not receive staking rewards. You will not be able to cancel the unbonding.

info.unstakingPeriodTooltip_noToken: The amount of time you must wait after unstaking before you can withdraw.

info.upgradeToV2Description: Upgrade your DAO to the v2 smart contracts. This supports SubDAOs and other new features.
info.upgradeToV2Explanation: This upgrades your DAO's contracts to the latest audited version. Below you may register any SubDAOs that were created while this DAO was using v1. SubDAOs can use any version, but v2 is recommended.
info.uploadSmartContractCodeActionDescription: Upload smart contract code to the chain for future instantiation.
info.useNativeCrossChainAccountInstead: This chain is supported by DAO DAO's native cross-chain accounts. We recommend avoiding ICA when possible. Click the button below to switch to our native cross-chain account action.
info.validatorActionsDescription: Make transactions related to running a validator.
info.vaultVotingPowerTooltip: The total voting power in the DAO derived from this voting vault.
info.verificationPendingResend: Verification pending. Click to resend email.

info.vestingCrossChainAccountCreationTooltip: Before you can create the required vesting payment manager, you must first create a cross-chain account for the DAO on the target chain, because the DAO's account must be set as the owner of the vesting manager. You will need to pass a proposal creating the account before you can set up vesting on the target chain in a subsequent proposal.
info.vestingIsCancellableByOther: This vesting payment can be cancelled by the following address after it's created.
info.vestingIsCancellableByOwner_dao: This vesting payment can be cancelled by the DAO after it's created.
info.vestingIsCancellableByOwner_wallet: You will be able to cancel this vesting payment after it's created.
info.vestingManagerExplanation: To create vesting payments, you must first create a vesting payment manager on each chain that you want to pay from, and the DAO must have an account on each chain before you can create the manager.
info.vestingManagerNeeded: To create a vesting payment on {{chain}}, the DAO must first setup a vesting payment manager by passing a proposal with the setup action. Click the button to add the setup action and remove this vesting payment.
info.vestingNotCancellable: This vesting payment cannot be cancelled later.
info.vestingPaymentsDescription: A vesting payment distributes funds according to any schedule you choose, and the DAO can enable or disable early cancelation.
info.vetoActionDaoMemberExplanation_withEarly: The buttons below will open the proposal creation page in the vetoer DAO, prefilled with the selected action. Nothing will happen until you submit, pass, and execute that proposal.
info.vetoActionDaoMemberExplanation_withoutEa: The button below will open the proposal creation page in the vetoer DAO, prefilled with the veto action. Nothing will happen until you submit, pass, and execute that proposal.
info.vetoDescription: Give veto authority to another DAO, allowing them to veto proposals passed by this DAO. Ensure the veto timelock duration is longer than the vetoer's voting period so they have time to pass their veto proposals.
info.vetoEarlyExecuteExplanation: If you do not want to veto this proposal, you may execute it early instead, skipping the rest of the veto timelock period. Otherwise, the proposal will be executable once the veto timelock period expires.
info.vetoOrEarlyExecuteDescription: Veto a proposal in another DAO that you have veto power over or early-execute if you decide not to veto (if early-execute is enabled).
info.vetoThresholdTooltip: A proposal must attain this proportion of 'No with Veto' votes to be vetoed.
info.vetoableProposalsTooltip: Proposals in other DAOs that this DAO ({{daoName}}) has the power to veto.
info.virtualVotingVaultTooltip: Virtual voting vaults do not support bonding tokens manually, instead deriving voting power from other sources.
info.voteOnGovernanceProposalDescription: Vote on an open chain governance proposal, as an individual or as a validator.
info.voteUntilExpirationExplanation: Although the proposal outcome is determined, you may cast a vote until the proposal expires to be included in the final tally.
info.votingDurationTooltip: The maximum amount of time proposals are open for voting.
info.votingDurationTooltip_noRevoting: The maximum amount of time proposals are open for voting. Because you are not allowed to change your vote, proposals can finalize early if sufficient votes are cast to guarantee an outcome.
info.votingDurationTooltip_revoting: The amount of time proposals are open for voting. Because you are allowed to change your vote, a proposal will always stay open this long.
info.votingModuleAdapterCreationDiscord: Want to help us support this voting module? Join the <2><0>DAO DAO Discord</0><1/></2> and post in #dao-help.
info.votingModuleNotYetSupported: This DAO uses a voting module that our UI does not yet support. Functionality may be limited.
info.votingPowerAtCreationTooltip: This was your voting power at the time of proposal creation.
info.votingVaultsExplanation: Voting power in the DAO derives from multiple sources.
info.waitingForRateAndPropose: Waiting for DAO members to rate and propose...
info.whatDoTheyWantToBeRated: What do they want to be rated?
info.whatDoYouWantToBeRated: What do you want to be rated?
info.withdrawTokenSwapDescription: Withdraw funds from a token swap that has not yet completed.
info.wouldYouLikeToSearchQuestion: Would you like to search for a DAO?
info.yourVaultVotingPowerTooltip: The voting power within this voting vault owned by you.

meta.description: Create a DAO to manage your community, protocol, or entire blockchain in just a few clicks. We support multisig, token-based, and NFT-based DAOs that can be as simple or complex as you want. Set up SubDAOs, manage interchain assets, and interact with dApps across the Cosmos.
